```java
if (UPN_OID.equals(tempOid)) {
    foundUpn = true;
    break;
}
```
Reason:
The patch introduces logic to specifically check for the UPN_OID within the 'otherName' type of SAN. By identifying the UPN correctly, the code ensures that user identities can be mapped accurately during authentication, thus resolving the bug.


